  "text": "where the \"experimental data\" c δ is the numerical solution computed with the scheme (8) with α set equal to the target valuesα and a very fine discretization in time and space δ, so that it correctly mimics the exact continuous solution of [CITATION_1] . The values c δ (t n ) are obtained by resampling this solution on the coarser grid of sampling t. This time, the global minimum ofJ δ is not trivially obtained inα, except for the limiting case for which t = δ, where we are back to the previous cost function (11) withJ δ (α) = 0. Here again we will numerically illustrate the convergence of the minimization algorithm as t goes to δ.",
